article.headline: Army 64, Lehigh 61
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Josh Miller scored 25 points, including nine of 10 free throw attempts, to lead Army to a 64-61 overtime victory over Lehigh on Wednesday. Jarell Brown added 13 points for Army (14-15, 6-8 Patriot League), which made 20 of 25 shots from the line. Bryan White had 21 points and 10 rebounds for Lehigh (14-15, 7-7). Marquis Hall contributed 15 points and Zahir Carrington accounted for 10. Matt Szalachowski hit a pair of free throws to give Lehigh a three-point lead 2:13 remaining in overtime. But Miller scored a pair of free throws of his own and then found Cleveland Richard to put the Black Knights ahead 62-61 with just over a minute remaining. Lehigh opened the second half with a 10-2 run to tie the game and later pulled ahead on a pair of free throws by Prentice Small with 9:50 remaining. The Mountain Hawks then went on a 12-3 run, with back-to-back layups from Carrington, to take a seven-point lead with just over six minutes to play. Army chipped away at the lead and tied the game on a dunk by Doug Williams with 22 seconds remaining to send the game into overtime.
